'''Seána Talbot''' is a former President of the UK charity [[National Childbirth Trust]] (NCT).<ref name=nct-new /> 

She first became a member of NCT in 1995.<ref name=nct-pcc>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nct.org.uk/press-release/nct-trustee-appointed-northern-ireland-pcc|title=NCT Trustee appointed to the Northern Ireland PCC {{!}} NCT|website=www.nct.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-03-03}}</ref> She was elected as a trustee in 2009.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://thirdforcenews.org.uk/features/goodmovers-who-is-going-where-in-the-voluntary-sector-5-october-2015|title=Goodmovers {{!}} Who is going where in the voluntary sector {{!}} 12 October 2015|work=Third Force News|access-date=2017-03-03|language=en}}</ref> Elected as President by NCT members in September 2015, at the [[Annual general meeting]].<ref name=nct-new>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nct.org.uk/press-release/new-leadership-team-nct|title=New leadership team at NCT {{!}} NCT|website=www.nct.org.uk|language=en|access-date=2017-03-02}}</ref> She was pressured into resigning along with a fellow trustee in December 2016, after a child died of [[cot death]] in a cot endorsed by the trust.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/childbirth-chief-faced-pressure-to-quit-after-cot-death-hm27khg60|title=Childbirth chief faced pressure to quit after cot death|access-date=2017-03-02|language=en}}</ref>

She has held various health management posts in [[Northern Ireland]], and in 2014, was appointed as Non-Executive Director on the Board of the Patient and Client Council (PCC).<ref name=nct-pcc />

